{"questionId":"11758","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urvashi wants to model the height of a moving object. She collects the following data showing the height, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\">\n  <mi>h</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; metres, of the object at time <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> seconds.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1b8ea3fd216ff6ca44f745b8e6644c5d437f1dbc.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">She believes the height can be modeled by a quadratic function,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\\left( t \\right) = a{t^2} + bt + c\">\n  <mi>h</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b{\\text{,}}\\,\\,c \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Solve this system of three equations to find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a =&nbsp; - \\frac{5}{3}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b = 13{\\text{,}}\\,\\,c = \\frac{{44}}{3}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>13</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>44</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11758","referenceCode":"EXM.2.SL.TZ0.3c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Solve this system of three equations to find the value of a , b and c .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}